Preliminary Program Announcement

NATIONAL SOFTWARE COUNCIL WORKSHOP

The National Security Industrial Association (NSIA) Software and Information
Systems Committee will host a workshop to plan and organize the National
Software Council.

NATIONAL SOFTWARE COUNCIL INITIATIVE

The National Software Council (NSC) is an initiative to organize and implement
a national advisory board reporting to the highest levels of government. The
Council will advise on major software issues, develop policy, and propose
national economic and technology initiatives.

WORKSHOP PROGRAM

What: The workshop will take place over a one and a half (1&1/2) day period.
It will revolve around panels that are organized based on the defined issues:
Legal, International, Societal, Economic, Education, and the NSC nominating
committee panel. This last panel will organize the NSC-Implementation
Committee (NSC-IC).

The NSC-IC will be responsible for carrying this task forward by finalizing
the charter for the NSC, organizing advocacy groups, and forming the NSC.
A Chair, Facilitator, and Speaker will be assigned to each panel. There will
be a plenary session that will include a welcome by Lloyd Mosemann, Deputy
Assistant Secretary of the Air Force for Communications, Computers, and
Support Systems.

Where: The workshop will be held at the Center for Adult Education of the
University of Maryland, College Park, Maryland.

When: October 26 and 27, 1994.

A final program will be mailed in September 1994.

