The second purpose, organizing the NSC-IC, will be accomplished through
nominations received as a result of this flyer and future mailings.

The formation of a NSC Organizing Committee, the NSC-IC, is a step called out
in the Planning Task Force report. The purpose of this step is to create a
broadly based committee, more representative of society than the NSIA SISC.
The NSC-IC, once organized, would be charged with defining, advocating,
organizing and implementing the NSC. The NSC-IC will be organized through
Panel F, the NSC-IC Nominating Panel.

Panel F has a different purpose than the previous ones as it does not deal
with a specific issue, but rather with the composition of, and nominations
for, the NSC-IC. The objective is to organize the NSC-IC at the workshop
so that it can immediately pursue the organization of the NSC. Two SISC
points of contact are assigned to this panel: Diane Miller, BDM,
703-848-6720 and Robert Wint, EDS, 703-276-3841

